HEAT vegetable oil in large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, for 2 to 3 minutes or until onion is tender. Add pasta; cook, stirring constantly, for 1 to 2 minutes or until pasta starts to turn golden. STIR in tomatoes with juice, broth, chiles, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 7 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Sprinkle with cheese just before serving.